## 6. User Stories & Acceptance Criteria

### Epic 1: Deck Discovery

**US-1.1 — Browse All Decks**
*As a visitor, I want to see all available presentations on the home page so I can discover what's available.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Home page renders a responsive grid: 1 col (mobile), 2 col (tablet), 3 col (desktop). |
| AC-2 | Each card displays: thumbnail/color swatch, title, 2-line description, tag chips, slide count. |
| AC-3 | Cards are keyboard-navigable (Tab to focus, Enter to open). |
| AC-4 | Page loads in < 2s on 3G (Lighthouse Performance ≥ 90). |
| AC-5 | Grid uses `NuxtLink` for client-side navigation (no full page reload). |

**US-1.2 — Search Decks**
*As a visitor, I want to search by title, description, or tag so I can quickly find a specific presentation.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Search input is above the fold with placeholder: "Search by title, description, or tags..." |
| AC-2 | Results filter in real-time (debounced 300ms, no page reload). |
| AC-3 | Search uses `queryContent` with `$icontains` for full-text matching across title, description, and tags. |
| AC-4 | Empty results show a friendly message: "No decks match your search." |
| AC-5 | Search input has `role="search"`, associated `<label>`, and visible focus ring (2px solid Emerald). |

**US-1.3 — Filter by Tag**
*As a visitor, I want to filter decks by category tag so I can narrow results by topic.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Tags render as horizontally scrollable chips below the search bar. |
| AC-2 | "All" tag is selected by default; tapping a tag toggles its active state. |
| AC-3 | Active tag has Emerald background with white text; inactive has `bg-gray-100` with `text-gray-700`. |
| AC-4 | Each tag shows a badge count of matching decks. |
| AC-5 | "Clear filters" link appears when any filter is active. |
| AC-6 | Filter state persists in URL query params (deep-linkable). |

**US-1.4 — Sort Decks**
*As a visitor, I want to sort decks by date or title so I can find the most recent or alphabetically ordered presentations.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Sort dropdown with options: "Newest First" (default), "Oldest First", "A → Z", "Z → A". |
| AC-2 | Sort selection persists across filter changes within the same session. |
| AC-3 | Dropdown is keyboard-accessible (arrow keys to navigate, Enter to select). |

---

### Epic 2: Deck Viewing

**US-2.1 — View Presentation**
*As a visitor, I want to view a Reveal.js presentation inline so I can preview slides without downloading.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Presentation renders in an `<iframe>` with `src="/reveals/:id.html"`. |
| AC-2 | iframe is responsive: min-height 400px (mobile), 500px+ (desktop), 16:9 aspect ratio preserved. |
| AC-3 | Slide counter displays "Slide X of Y" below the viewer. |
| AC-4 | Arrow keys navigate slides when iframe is focused. |
| AC-5 | `sandbox` attribute on iframe allows scripts but prevents top navigation. |

**US-2.2 — Fullscreen Mode**
*As a presenter, I want to enter fullscreen so I can use the deck in a live presentation.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | "Fullscreen" button (44×44px min touch target) is visible near the viewer. |
| AC-2 | Uses the Fullscreen API; falls back gracefully on unsupported browsers. |
| AC-3 | ESC key exits fullscreen; an explicit "Exit Fullscreen" button is also available. |
| AC-4 | Fullscreen button has `aria-label="Enter fullscreen mode"` that updates to "Exit fullscreen mode". |

**US-2.3 — View Deck Metadata**
*As a visitor, I want to see metadata (description, tags, stats) alongside the presentation so I understand the deck's context.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Desktop: 2-column layout — viewer (70%) + sticky sidebar (30%, 280–320px). |
| AC-2 | Mobile: sidebar stacks below the viewer. |
| AC-3 | Sidebar displays: description, tags, slide count, estimated duration, created date, last modified, event history, and current version label. |
| AC-4 | Tags in sidebar are clickable and navigate back to home with that tag pre-filtered. |

**US-2.5 — Switch Deck Versions**
*As a visitor, I want to switch between versions of a presentation so I can see how a talk evolved across events.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | `VersionSelector` dropdown appears below the viewer when `versions.length > 1`. |
| AC-2 | Each option shows: version label + date (e.g., "v2 — OrlandoCodeCamp26 Update · Mar 2026"). |
| AC-3 | Selecting a version reloads the iframe `src` to the corresponding `revealFile` without a page reload. |
| AC-4 | If a version has a `changes` field, a brief changelog appears below the selector. |
| AC-5 | The `currentVersion` loads by default; URL does not change on version switch (version state is ephemeral). |
| AC-6 | Dropdown is hidden (not disabled) when only one version exists. |

**US-2.4 — Navigate Back to Home**
*As a visitor, I want a clear way to return to the deck listing so I can browse other presentations.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Breadcrumb "Home > Deck Title" is sticky at the top of the deck page. |
| AC-2 | "Home" link preserves scroll position and active filters via browser history API. |
| AC-3 | Browser back button returns to previous scroll position on home page. |

