### Epic 4: Accessibility (WCAG 2.2 AA)

**US-4.1 — Keyboard Navigation**
*As a keyboard user, I want full tab-order navigation so I can use the site without a mouse.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Tab order: skip link → search → filters → sort → deck cards → footer. [WCAG 2.4.3] |
| AC-2 | All interactive elements have visible focus rings (2–4px, Emerald). [WCAG 2.4.7, 2.4.11] |
| AC-3 | Minimum touch/click target size: 24×24px (Level AA). [WCAG 2.5.8] |
| AC-4 | Deck cards are focusable and activate on Enter/Space. |

**US-4.2 — Screen Reader Support**
*As a screen reader user, I want semantic markup so I can understand the page structure.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | Home page uses `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<h1>`–`<h3>` hierarchy. [WCAG 1.3.1] |
| AC-2 | Deck cards use `role="article"` or semantic `<article>` elements. |
| AC-3 | Search input has visible `<label>` or `aria-label`. [WCAG 1.3.1] |
| AC-4 | Filter tags use `aria-pressed` to indicate active state. [WCAG 4.1.2] |
| AC-5 | Deck thumbnails have `alt="Preview of {Deck Title}"`. [WCAG 1.1.1] |

**US-4.3 — Color & Contrast**
*As a low-vision user, I want sufficient contrast so I can read all text.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | All body text meets 4.5:1 contrast ratio. [WCAG 1.4.3] |
| AC-2 | All UI components (borders, icons) meet 3:1 contrast ratio. [WCAG 1.4.11] |
| AC-3 | Color is never the sole indicator of active state (text/icon supplement required). [WCAG 1.4.1] |
| AC-4 | Dark mode maintains equivalent contrast ratios. |

**US-4.4 — Reduced Motion**
*As a motion-sensitive user, I want animations to respect my OS settings.*

| # | Acceptance Criteria |
|---|---|
| AC-1 | All CSS transitions/animations are wrapped in `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)`. [WCAG 2.3.3] |
| AC-2 | Card hover effects degrade to instant state change when reduced motion is active. |

